<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="68.[124,653,193,920]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet is a Latin adjective meaning ‘‘stretch out’’. I refer to the extended condition of the posterior patch of the elytral middiscal setal tuft.</paragraph>
